  "prompt": "How much electricity does a factory use?",
  "response": "The amount of electricity a factory uses can vary widely depending on several factors including the size of the factory, the type of industry, the number of machines and equipment, operating hours, and energy efficiency measures. \n\nFor instance:\n- A small factory with limited equipment may use a few thousand kilowatt-hours (kWh) per month.\n- A medium-sized factory might use tens of thousands of kWh per month.\n- Large manufacturing plants with heavy machinery and continuous operation could use hundreds of thousands to millions of kWh per month.\n\nTo get an accurate measure of electricity usage for a specific factory, it's essential to conduct an energy audit or review the factory's utility bills. This assessment can help identify consumption patterns and potential areas for improving energy efficiency.",
